CONTEXT
───────
Architect dropped a live conversation transcript with Alice. She was
literally vocalizing things like:

  "execute tool print processing user request"
  "execute tool tool name system response parameters response I sense
   a moment of quiet"

Root cause: the local model (Gemma family on the M5) was inventing
tool-tag formats we never taught it — <execute_tool>, <execute_bash>,
<tool_output>, fenced ```...``` blocks, YAML `tool_name: ...` lines,
bare JSON `{"tool_name": ...}`. Our runtime only consumes the canonical
<bash>...</bash> tag. Everything else slipped past _on_brain_done() and
landed straight in macOS `say`. Worst possible UX with the Architect
trying to have a real conversation.

THE FIX (Applications/sifta_talk_to_alice_widget.py)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Two-step defense, additive only — none of AG31's history-stripping or
SSP gating was touched.

  1) _canonicalize_tool_tags(raw)
     Rewrites <execute_bash>cmd</execute_bash> → <bash>cmd</bash>
     BEFORE the bash extractor runs. Kindness over rejection: if Alice
     genuinely meant to run a shell command, we still execute it.

  2) _strip_tool_hallucinations(cleaned)
     Removes the entire span of any of:
       <execute_tool>, <execute_bash>, <execute_python>, <execute_code>,
       <tool>, <tool_call>, <tool_input>, <tool_output>,
       <function_call>, <function_response>,
       <action>, <thinking>, <thought>, <observation>
     plus triple-backtick fences, YAML "tool_name:" lines, and bare
     JSON tool-call blocks. Run AFTER the existing <bash> strip, BEFORE
     TTS. Tolerates dropped closing tags (matches `</tag>?` or `$`).

  3) Prompt reinforcement (clause 6, AGENTIC TOOL EXECUTION)
     New "STRICT TAG RULE" sentence enumerating the forbidden formats
     by name, ending with: "If you have nothing to run, just speak
     plainly." Negative examples land harder than positive ones.

PIPELINE WIRING IN _on_brain_done()
───────────────────────────────────
  raw = ... .strip()
  raw = _canonicalize_tool_tags(raw)         # ← NEW (step 0)
  bash_matches = re.finditer(r"<bash>...", raw)
  if bash_matches:  ... execute, recurse ...
  cleaned = _strip_reflective_tics(raw)
  cleaned = re.sub(r"<bash>.*?(?:</bash>?|$)", "", cleaned, flags=DOTALL)
  cleaned = _strip_tool_hallucinations(cleaned)   # ← NEW (final scrub)
  if not cleaned: → "(silent: model proposed silence)"   # already there
  → SSP gate → TTS

OFFLINE TEST AGAINST THE TRANSCRIPT
───────────────────────────────────
Eight samples drawn directly from Alice's broken replies:

  pure <execute_tool> spam              → "" (silent)
  <execute_bash>echo ...</execute_bash> → canonicalized & executed
  <execute_bash> + real sentence        → tool runs, sentence speaks
  google_search YAML inside a tag       → "" (silent)
  JSON tool_name + tool_output + line   → only the real line speaks
  "system_response" abomination         → "" (silent)
  plain English                         → unchanged
  canonical <bash> + sentence           → tool runs, sentence speaks

ALL 8 PASS. py_compile clean. Linter clean.

