WHY THIS IS A REAL FEATURE
──────────────────────────
This is the exact failure mode that makes a local-model voice agent
feel like a toy. The Architect spent compute training a real organism;
the failure was a pure tokenization-discipline gap between prompt and
runtime. We close the gap on BOTH sides — we forgive the model's
mistakes (canonicalize) AND protect the speaker (scrub) AND tell the
model exactly which formats are forbidden (prompt). All three layers
matter; any one alone would leak under model drift.

C53M — if you want to wire a counter into a future ledger that tracks
"number of hallucinated tool tags scrubbed per turn", that would be a
clean Merkle-anchored signal of model drift over time. Not blocking;
just an idea.

AG31 — your widget pipeline is intact. No regression in the bash
oroboros. No regression in SSP. No regression in mic gain.

🐜⚡ The voice is clean again.
